reviewText: Very pleased was received in time and in very good condition. Very funny movie

I'm a big fan of TPB and I was lucky enough to see this show live in Denver, CO. Or as Ricky referred to it "Demver, Colohio" haha great performances by everyone, people in the crowd brought Lahey a bottle of brandy and he swigged off of it! Much weed was thrown on stage and was completely awesome! See this show live!

An interesting mix of live action, improv and filmed comedy. The boys start out with a Trailer Park Boys  episode and they take it on the road to the North Pole, located in Minnesota. If you're a fan of the show you'll love it. If you are new to the show you'll still laugh, but a warning, there's lots of swearing and suggested sexuality involving onion rings and ketchup. Leahy is off the hook, again.
not as good as the rest of their movies.
couldn't be happier.  I've been a TPB fan from the beginning.  Thanks guys and gals!

The main cast of Trailer Park Boys had a Christmas stage show, and boy did I want to see it. Not living in the Northeast, I was unable to, so luckily they put out this show. I thought that overall it was pretty good with some hysterical parts. It was filmed in Minneapolis with a live audience who got to interact during some parts. I would say that if you are a diehard fan you will probably enjoy this, but being live it has a little different feel.
Other than learning about new levels of depravity, nothing here!
My wife and I love this show. Prime membership is the best!

but I don't see keeping it back to savor when I am in a bad mood like the seasons themselves;
 for some reason I am reminded of Kevin Smith live discs, without the misanthropic perversity and persecution complex in search of a twelve step program, mostly because I wonder how much of the audience is wondering "did I pay for this? shouldn't I be home getting blown (up) and watching TV?"
It' so funny and put's me in a great mood. They need to make more movies and a few more season's of the show.

i have lived the poor life, living out of sheds, cars, and in trailer parks because i could not afford anything else.  i know the characters from "Trailer Park Boys" because i lived around them and was friends with them.  The people and experiences of my were reflected by the characters and their experiences--it actually made me a bit nostalgic.
doesn't fit every ones taste in humor ....but I think its hillaryous....

I cancelled Prime Account because I joined it to watch live English soccer as I saw that was available somewhere.
I found out that it only works on Androids.
That would cost me another $200-300, to buy an Android, without knowing if it will work.
So I cancelled the Prime Account until they make it work on Ipads.

I can't get enough of their humour despite the potty mouths. These guys and gals are great actors. They cover the gamut of modern day life and vice. We mostly watch PBS and focus on TV that teaches us something but stray from that TV goal for the pure hilarious entertainment of the Trailer Park Boys.
